      "content": "The CREST client is actually one of our biggest revenue drivers. If they churn, it's going to be a massive hit to the quarter. I honestly don't think a template system can handle the nuance required to keep them happy—it'll probably just give them generic answers and make them even more frustrated. It feels like a huge risk to just pull the plug on the LLM right when things are getting complicated. Do you really think it's better to just switch to the cheaper option now, or is there a middle ground we're missing?",
